ds City Council]] in the [[City of Leeds]], [[West Yorkshire]], [[England]] is elected each year, followed by no election in one year out of every four years. A total of 99 [[councillors|councillors]] have been elected from 33 [[electoral wards]] across [[Leeds]] since [[1980 Leeds City Council election|1980]].<ref name=councillors>{{cite web | url = http://www.leeds.gov.uk/Council_and_democracy/Councillors_democracy_and_elections/Councillors__information_and_advice.aspx | title = Councillors' roles and responsibilities | accessdate = 7 February 2010 | publisher = Leeds City Council| url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100219103501/http://www.leeds.gov.uk/Council_and_democracy/Councillors_democracy_and_elections/Councillors__information_and_advice.aspx | archivedate = 19 February 2010 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Political control==\n[[File:Leed - seat totals.png|thumb|539px|right|Seat totals, 1973\u20132012]]\nSince 1973 political control of the council has been held by the following parties:<ref name=change>{{cite news| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/bsp/hi/elections/local_council/08/html/da.stm | title = Leeds | accessdate = 7 February 2010 | publisher = [[BBC News Online]]| date=19 April 2008}}</ref>\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n! Party in control || Administration || Years\n|- ! style=\"background-color: #CCCCCC\"\n| [[No overall control]] || Labour minority || 1973\u20131976\n|- ! style=\"background-color: #5B76FF\"\n| [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] || Conservative majority || 1976\u20131979\n|- ! style=\"background-color: #CCCCCC\"\n| [[No overall control]] || Conservative minority || 1979\u20131980\n|- ! style=\"background-color: #FF6868\"\n| [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] || Labour majority || 1980\u20132004\n|- ! style=\"background-color: #CCCCCC\"\n| rowspan=2 | [[No overall control]] || [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Lib Dem]]-Conservative Coalition || 2004\u20132010\n|- ! style=\"background-color: #CCCCCC\"\n| Labour minority || 2010\u20132011\n|- ! style=\"background-color: #FF6868\"\n| [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] || Labour majority || 2011\u2013present\n|}\n\n==Council elections==\n\nSummary of the council composition after council elections, click on the year for full details of each election. Boundary changes took place for the 1980 election which increased the number of seats by 3, leading to the whole council being elected in that year. Further boundary changes made in 2004 again required the full council to be elected.<ref name=leeds>{{cite news| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/bsp/hi/vote2004/locals/html/3712.stm | title =Leeds council | accessdate = 24 September 2008 | publisher = [[BBC Online]]}}</ref>\n<br />\n[[File:Leeds - vote shares.png|thumb|500px|right|Popular vote shares, 1973\u20132012]]\n[[File:Leeds - vote totals.png|thumb|500px|right|Popular vote figures, 1973\u20132012]]\n<br />\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 0em 0em 0em 0em; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n| Year\n!style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}; width: 3px;\" |\n|width=\"60\"|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n!style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}; width: 3px;\" |\n|width=\"60\"|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n!style=\"background-color: {{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}; width: 3px;\" |\n|width=\"60\"|[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]\n!style=\"background-color: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}; width: 3px;\" |\n|width=\"60\"|[[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n!style=\"background-color: {{Green Party of England and Wales/meta/color}}; width: 3px;\" |\n|width=\"60\"|[[Green Party of England and Wales|Greens]]\n!style=\"background-color: {{Morley Borough Independent/meta/color}}; width: 3px;\" |\n|width=\"60\"|[[Morley Borough Independents]]\n!style=\"background-color: {{British National Party/meta/color}}; width: 3px;\" |\n|width=\"60\"|[[British National Party|BNP]]\n|-\n| [[1973 Leeds City Council election|1973]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 44\n|colspan=\"2\"| 38\n|colspan=\"2\"| 14\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1975 Leeds City Council election|1975]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 41\n|colspan=\"2\"| 43\n|colspan=\"2\"| 12\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1976 Leeds City Council election|1976]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 38\n|colspan=\"2\"| 50\n|colspan=\"2\"| 8\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1978 Leeds City Council election|1978]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 39\n|colspan=\"2\"| 50\n|colspan=\"2\"| 7\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1979 Leeds City Council election|1979]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 44\n|colspan=\"2\"| 45\n|colspan=\"2\"| 7\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1980 Leeds City Council election|1980]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 62\n|colspan=\"2\"| 29\n|colspan=\"2\"| 8\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1982 Leeds City Council election|1982]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 56\n|colspan=\"2\"| 32\n|colspan=\"2\"| 11\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1983 Leeds City Council election|1983]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 54\n|colspan=\"2\"| 33\n|colspan=\"2\"| 11\n|colspan=\"2\"| 1\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1984 Leeds City Council election|1984]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 53\n|colspan=\"2\"| 33\n|colspan=\"2\"| 12\n|colspan=\"2\"| 1\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|colspan=\"2\"| 0\n|-\n| [[1986 Leeds City Council election|1986]]\n|colspan=\"2\"| 58\n|colspan=\"2\"| 28\n|colspan=\"2\"| 11\n|colspan=\"2\"| 2\n|colspan=\"2