debuilt database|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> sank under tow 27th.\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Cetus'' (1920)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|Norway}}\n|align=\"right\"|2,614\n|align=\"left\"|HX\n|align=\"left\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Chama'' (1938)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|8,077\n|align=\"left\"|BHX 65\n|align=\"left\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''City of Hankow'' (1915)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|7,360\n|align=\"left\"|SHX\n|align=\"left\"|Bombed 26 August, but made port\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Conus'' (1931)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|8,132\n|align=\"left\"|BHX 65\n|align=\"left\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Cymbula'' (1938)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|8,082\n|align=\"left\"|BHX 65\n|align=\"left\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Eclipse'' (1931)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|9,767\n|align=\"left\"|BHX 65\n|align=\"left\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''[[List of Empire ships (M)#Empire Merlin|Empire Merlin]]'' (1919)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|5,763\n|align=\"left\"|BHX 65\n|align=\"left\"|Straggled:<ref>Hague lists ''Empire Merlin'' as a straggler; Uboat.net states she was in convoy when hit</ref> sunk 25 August by {{GS|U-48|1939|2}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/485.html|title=Empire Merlin \u2013 British steam merchant|publisher=www.uboat.net|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> 35 dead, 1 survivor\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''F J Wolfe'' (1932)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|12,190\n|align=\"left\"|BHX 65\n|align=\"left\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Fernbank'' (1924)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|Norway}}\n|align=\"right\"|4,333\n|align=\"left\"|HX\n|align=\"left\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''Fircrest'' (1907)\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|align=\"right\"|5,394\n|align=\"left\"|HX\n|align=\"left\"|Cargo of 