 787-8 Dreamliner|website=United.com|accessdate=2013-03-26}}</ref>\n|To be retrofitted with new Polaris seats and Premium Plus seats.\n<!--------- begin row --------->\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Boeing 787-9]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |28\n| rowspan=\"2\" |10\n|48\n| rowspan=\"2\" |&mdash;\n|21\n|39\n|149\n|257\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.united.com/ual/en/us/fly/travel/inflight/aircraft/787-900.html#v2|title=United Airlines - Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner|website=United.com|accessdate=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|48\n|&mdash;\n|88\n|116\n|252\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.united.com/web/en-US/content/travel/inflight/aircraft/787/900/default.aspx|title=United Airlines - Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner|website=United.com|accessdate=2014-03-28}}</ref>\n|Remaining aircraft on order will be delivered with new Polaris seats and Premium Plus cabin.<br>Existing aircraft to be retrofitted with new Polaris seats and Premium Plus cabins.\n<!--------- begin row --------->\n|-\n|[[Boeing 787-10]]\n|13\n|1\n|44\n|&mdash;\n|21\n|54\n|199\n|318\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.united.com/web/en-US/content/travel/inflight/aircraft/787/10/default.aspx|title=Boeing 787-10 Dreamliner Seat Map|website=United.com|access-date=February 21, 2019}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n!Total\n!801\n!267\n! colspan=\"8\" |\n|}\n\nIn a 2019 United Enhanced [[Equipment Trust Certificate]], a new [[Embraer E-175|Embraer 175]] mean valuation is $30.6-30.7 million, a [[Boeing 737 MAX]]-9 is $51.9-52.7 million and a [[Boeing 787-10]] is $155.5- 156.3 million.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.aircraftvaluenews.com/united-2eetc-019-1-highlights-difference-in-value-of-even-new-aircraft/ |title= United 2EETC 019-1 Highlights Difference In Value of Even New Aircraft |author= Aircraft Value News |date= May 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Historical fleet==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:auto; text-align:center;\"\n|+United Airlines former fleet<ref name=\":1\" />\n|- \n!Aircraft\n!Total\n!Introduced\n!Retired\n!Replacement\n!Notes\n|-\n|[[Boeing 40A]]\n|{{Unknown}}\n|1927\n|1937\n|{{Unknown}}\n|Launch customer<br>Operated by [[Boeing Air Transport]]<ref>Bohl, Walt: [http://home.comcast.net/~biplane0/boeing40/Boeing40paper2.pdf Boeing model 40 and its descendants]{{dead link|date=May 2017|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref> and [[Varney Air Lines]]\n|-\n|[[Boeing 80|Boeing 80A]]\n|{{Unknown}}\n|1928\n|1934\n|{{Unknown}}\n|Launch customer<br>Operated by Boeing Air Transport\n|-\n|[[Boeing 247]]\n|{{Unknown}}\n|1933\n|1942\n|{{Unknown}}\n|Launch customer<br>All 59 of the base model were built for [[United Airlines]]<ref>{{cite book|url=//books.google.com/books?id=2zTueJhXW0QC&lpg=PP19&pg=PA192#v=onepage&q=&f=false|title=The Boeing 247: the first modern ... \u2013 Google Books|last=Seely|first=Victor J.|date=1991-12-01|publisher=|year=|isbn=9780295970943|location=|pages=|accessdate=May 3, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Boeing 377 Stratocruiser]]\n|{{Unknown}}\n|{{Unknown}}\n|1954\n|{{Unknown}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 720]]\n|{{Unknown}}\n|1960\n|1976\n|[[Boeing 727]]\n|Launch Customer.\n|-\n|[[Boeing 727-100]]\n|126\n|1963\n|1993\n|[[Airbus A320 family]]<br>[[Boeing 737 Classic]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 727-200]]\n|104\n|1968\n|2001\n|[[Airbus A320 family]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 737-200]]\n|101\n|1968\n|2001\n|[[Airbus A320 family]]\n|Launch Customer.\n|-\n|[[Boeing 737-300]]\n|103\n|1986\n|2009\n|[[Airbus A320 family]]\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Boeing 737-500]]<ref>{{cite news|title=United retired its last three B737-500s by end of May|url=http://www.ch-aviation.ch/portal/news/19395-united-retired-its-last-three-b737-500s-by-end-of-may|accessdate=5 June 2013|newspaper=ch-aviation}}</ref> \n|rowspan=\"2\"|102\n|1990\n|2009\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Airbus A320 family]]<br>[[Boeing 737 Next Generation|Boeing 737 NG]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Several [[737-500]]s were taken over from the merger with [[Continental Airlines]].\n|-\n|2011\n|2013\n|-\n|[[Boeing 747-100]]\n|23\n|1970\n|1999\n|[[Boeing 747-400]]<br>[[Boeing 777|B